THE FIVE CLASSIFICATIONS:
Each person's Resolve Energy falls primarily into ONE classification based on their Conviction's nature.

1. ASSERTION

Philosophy: "I impose my will on reality"
Expression: Overwhelming force, unstoppable momentum, direct power
Examples: Aka (momentum), Jiro (blade strikes), Yuki (pressure)
2. NEGATION

Philosophy: "I deny what opposes me"
Expression: Barriers, nullification, suppression, zone control
Examples: Captain (Unyielding Zone), Ren (Dulling Field), Tetsu (Rejection)
3. REDIRECTION

Philosophy: "I change the flow"
Expression: Momentum manipulation, force redirection, control
Examples: Yuki Morita (Momentum Drag), potential martial artists
4. MANIFESTATION

Philosophy: "I create from my will"
Expression: Elemental creation, constructs, projection
Examples: Kaito (fire), Sara (lightning), ranged fighters
5. TRANSMUTATION

Philosophy: "I transform what is"
Expression: Healing, adaptation, matter change, self-modification
Examples: Daichi (healing flames), shapeshifters, adapters
üéØ CLASSIFICATION RULES:
‚úÖ Everyone has ONE primary classification ‚úÖ Your Conviction determines your classification (not your choice) ‚úÖ Abilities within classifications vary wildly (fire ‚â† lightning, but both are Manifestation) ‚úÖ Advanced users can develop hybrid techniques (Daichi uses Transmutation + Manifestation) ‚úÖ Classifications interact tactically (some counter others)

‚öîÔ∏è CLASSIFICATION INTERACTIONS (Rock-Paper-Scissors-ish):
ASSERTION strong against:

Manifestation (overpowers constructs)
Redirection (too much force to redirect)
ASSERTION weak against:

Negation (walls stop momentum)
Transmutation (adapts to force)
NEGATION strong against:

Assertion (blocks force)
Manifestation (nullifies constructs)
NEGATION weak against:

Transmutation (changes around barriers)
Redirection (flows around defense)
REDIRECTION strong against:

Assertion (uses enemy's force)
Negation (bypasses static defense)
REDIRECTION weak against:

Transmutation (no consistent force to redirect)
Manifestation (too many angles)
MANIFESTATION strong against:

Redirection (overwhelming options)
Transmutation (ranged advantage)
MANIFESTATION weak against:

Negation (nullified)
Assertion (overpowered)
TRANSMUTATION strong against:

Negation (adapts around it)
Assertion (absorbs/converts force)
TRANSMUTATION weak against:

Manifestation (outranged)
Redirection (adaptive flow beats adaptation)
Not perfect counters‚Äîjust tactical advantages.

