‚ö° THE FIVE CLASSIFICATIONS (FINAL):
1. ASSERTION
Philosophy: "I impose my will on reality"

How it manifests:

Overwhelming force
Unstoppable momentum
Direct power application
Breaking through obstacles
Ability Types (examples):

Momentum manipulation (Aka)
Kinetic strikes (Jiro)
Pressure waves
Explosive force
Weight manipulation
Impact enhancement
Combat Style: Aggressive, forward, relentless

Weakness: Predictable, can be redirected or negated

2. NEGATION
Philosophy: "I deny what opposes me"

How it manifests:

Barriers and shields
Nullification fields
Suppression zones
Rejecting attacks/effects
Ability Types (examples):

Zone control (Captain Kurosawa)
Dulling fields (Ren)
Foresight/Rejection (Tetsu - Host)
Gravity negation
Sound dampening
Energy absorption
Combat Style: Defensive, reactive, immovable

Weakness: Limited offense, can be overwhelmed or bypassed

3. REDIRECTION
Philosophy: "I change the flow"

How it manifests:

Momentum manipulation (defensive)
Force redirection
Flow control
Tactical repositioning
Ability Types (examples):

Momentum Drag (Yuki Morita)
Velocity theft
Trajectory alteration
Counter-force generation
Energy circulation
Deflection mastery
Combat Style: Tactical, adaptive, uses enemy's strength

Weakness: Requires existing force to work with, struggles against pure defense or adaptation

4. MANIFESTATION
Philosophy: "I create from my will"

How it manifests:

Elemental generation
Energy constructs
Projection attacks
Creating matter from Resolve
Ability Types (examples):

Fire (Kaito)
Lightning (Sara)
Ice constructs
Wind blades
Shadow manipulation
Light projection
Weapon creation
Combat Style: Versatile, ranged, overwhelming options

Weakness: Energy intensive, can be nullified or overpowered

5. TRANSMUTATION
Philosophy: "I transform what is"

How it manifests:

Healing and restoration
Matter transformation
Self-modification
Adaptation and change
Ability Types (examples):

Healing flames (Daichi)
Body enhancement
Material conversion
Regeneration
Shapeshifting
Environmental alteration
Organic manipulation
Combat Style: Adaptive, supportive, endurance-focused

Weakness: Usually not directly offensive, requires time/contact

‚öîÔ∏è CLASSIFICATION INTERACTIONS (TACTICAL ADVANTAGES):
ASSERTION ‚Üî NEGATION

Assertion struggles against walls but breaks through weak barriers
Negation stops momentum but can be overwhelmed by sustained force
ASSERTION ‚Üî REDIRECTION

Redirection uses Assertion's force against it
But overwhelming Assertion overpowers redirection capacity
NEGATION ‚Üî MANIFESTATION

Negation nullifies constructs and projections
Manifestation can overwhelm with quantity/variety
MANIFESTATION ‚Üî TRANSMUTATION

Manifestation outranges Transmutation
Transmutation can adapt to and absorb Manifestation
REDIRECTION ‚Üî TRANSMUTATION

Redirection beats rigid Transmutation
Adaptive Transmutation has no consistent flow to redirect
Not hard counters‚Äîjust tactical considerations in combat.

