I'll give you a list of potential universal techniques. You tell me:

Which ones to KEEP
Which ones to REMOVE
Which ones to ADD
üìã PROPOSED UNIVERSAL TECHNIQUES:
1. RESOLVE SENSE (Passive/Active)
What it is:

Ability to sense other Resolve users' energy
Feel their location, strength, emotional state
Range increases with experience
Mechanics:

Passive: Always "on" for nearby strong sources
Active: Focus to extend range and detail
Can be masked by skilled users
Variations by skill level:

Beginner: "Someone powerful is nearby"
Intermediate: "Three users, northeast, one is angry"
Advanced: "That's Sara, 400m away, she's scared"
Master: Can sense Core type, damage, Conviction clarity
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

2. RESOLVE EMISSION (Active)
What it is:

Releasing your Resolve Energy as pressure/aura
Intimidation, communication, territory marking
Can physically pressure weaker users
Mechanics:

Projects your "presence" outward
Weaker users feel weight, fear, or awe
Can be shaped (threatening, calming, focused)
Combat applications:

Psychological warfare
Buying time
Warning shots
"Back off or else"
Variations:

Controlled emission (surgical precision)
Explosive emission (blast of pressure)
Sustained emission (maintaining dominance)
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

3. RESOLVE REINFORCEMENT (Active)
What it is:

Basic enhancement using Resolve Energy
Strengthens body, weapons, or objects
Foundation of all physical combat
Mechanics:

Channel Resolve Energy into specific body parts/items
Increases durability, strength, speed
Most common technique
Applications:

Punch harder
Move faster
Tank hits
Reinforce weapons so they don't break
Skill progression:

Beginner: Full-body reinforcement (inefficient, draining)
Intermediate: Targeted reinforcement (hands, legs, core)
Advanced: Instant switching (reinforce right before impact)
Master: Partial reinforcement (specific muscle groups mid-motion)
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

4. CORE PROTECTION (Passive/Active)
What it is:

Instinctively guarding your chest (where Core is located)
Fundamental survival technique
Mechanics:

Passive: Natural defensive reflex
Active: Conscious reinforcement of Core area
Creates thin barrier around chest
Why it matters:

Core damage = permanent injury or death
Experienced fighters target Cores
Protecting it is life-or-death
Skill levels:

Beginner: Obvious, telegraphed protection
Intermediate: Subtle, doesn't affect combat flow
Advanced: Can maintain while attacking
Master: Reflexive, even when unconscious
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

5. RESOLVE SUPPRESSION (Active)
What it is:

Hiding your Resolve signature
Stealth technique
Mechanics:

Reduces your detectable energy output
Makes you "invisible" to Resolve Sense
Requires focus and control
Applications:

Infiltration
Ambushes
Hiding from stronger opponents
Blending in with normal humans
Limitations:

Can't fight while suppressed (contradicts emission)
Advanced users can still detect you
Fractured/Lost can't do this (too unstable)
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

6. RESOLVE RECOVERY MEDITATION (Active)
What it is:

Deliberate rest technique to restore depleted Resolve Energy
Speeds up natural recovery
Mechanics:

Requires stillness and safety
Focuses inward, reignites Conviction
Restores energy faster than passive rest
Recovery rates:

Natural rest: hours to days
Basic meditation: cuts time in half
Advanced meditation: significant recovery in 30 minutes
Master level: combat recovery (brief moments of focus mid-fight)
Limitations:

Can't be used if Core is damaged
Requires safety (can't do in active combat)
Fractured users recover slower
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

7. RESOLVE FLARE (Active - Desperation Move)
What it is:

Explosive release of remaining Resolve Energy
Last-ditch escape or attack
Mechanics:

Burns through remaining energy in one burst
Creates shockwave, blast, or sudden power spike
Leaves you depleted afterward
Uses:

Breaking free from restraints
Creating opening to escape
Kamikaze attack
Forcing enemy back
Risk:

Empties your reserves
Vulnerable afterward
Can damage your own Core if reckless
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

8. RESOLVE CONTRACT (BASIC) (Strategic)
What it is:

Self-imposed limitation for temporary power boost
"If I do X, I get Y boost"
Mechanics:

You set a condition
While condition is active, you gain power
Breaking condition = power loss + penalty
Examples:

"I can only use Resolve with my right hand" ‚Üí left hand attacks are stronger
"I won't retreat during this fight" ‚Üí offense boosted, defense lowered
"I can only attack after being hit first" ‚Üí counters are devastating
Limitations:

Advanced technique (not beginner-friendly)
Requires clear Conviction
Breaking contract damages Core temporarily
Keep this? YES / NO / MODIFY

