‚úÖ LOCKED - THE FOUR UNIVERSAL TECHNIQUES
‚ö° UNIVERSAL TECHNIQUES (FINAL):
These are the ONLY techniques every Resolve user can learn, regardless of classification.

1. RESOLVE SENSE (Passive/Active)
What it is:

Ability to sense other Resolve users' presence and energy
Mechanics:

Passive: Always "on" for nearby strong sources
Active: Focus to extend range
ONLY SENSING - you feel "someone is there" and roughly how strong
CANNOT identify WHO it is (no names, no faces, no personal recognition)
Can sense general direction and distance
Can sense power level (weak, moderate, strong, overwhelming)
Skill Progression:

Beginner: Vague awareness within 50m
Intermediate: Clear sensing within 200m, vague beyond
Advanced: Precise sensing within 500m, directional awareness up to 1km
Master: Can sense across entire city districts, distinguish multiple signatures
Limitations:

Cannot identify individuals (just "a Resolve user")
Can be overwhelmed by too many sources
Naturals can mask their presence partially
The Lost emit chaotic, painful signatures
Everyone has this. It's survival instinct.

2. RESOLVE EMISSION (Active)
What it is:

Releasing your Resolve Energy as pressure/aura
Projects your presence outward
Mechanics:

Controlled release of energy
Can be shaped: threatening, calming, focused, wild
Weaker users feel physical pressure (weight, fear, difficulty breathing)
Equal-strength users feel intensity but not pressure
Stronger users barely notice
Combat Applications:

Intimidation
Territory marking ("this is my zone")
Warning without words
Psychological warfare
Buying time
Communicating intent
Skill Levels:

Beginner: Uncontrolled bursts, emotional leakage
Intermediate: Sustained, controlled emission
Advanced: Shaped emission (directional, targeted)
Master: Weaponized emission (pressure alone can incapacitate)
Examples:

Captain Kurosawa's golden aura = constant controlled emission
Aka's killing intent spikes = aggressive emission bursts
Shin's cold presence = effortless, oppressive emission
Everyone can do this, but skill varies wildly.

3. RESOLVE RECOVERY MEDITATION (Active)
What it is:

Deliberate rest technique to restore depleted Resolve Energy
Speeds up natural recovery
Mechanics:

Requires stillness, safety, and focus
Reconnect with your Conviction
Circulate dormant Anima back into your Core
Accelerates natural healing
Recovery Rates:

Natural rest (no meditation): 6-12 hours for moderate depletion, days for severe
Basic meditation: Cuts time in half
Intermediate meditation: 1-2 hours for moderate depletion
Advanced meditation: 30 minutes for significant recovery
Master meditation: Can recover mid-combat during brief pauses (extremely rare)
Requirements:

Safe environment (can't meditate while being attacked)
Mental clarity (panic/rage blocks it)
Intact Core (damaged Cores recover slower or not at all)
Special Cases:

Fractured users recover 30% slower (unstable Cores)
Naturals recover 20% faster (refined control)
The Lost cannot recover (no Conviction to anchor)
This is how fighters survive prolonged missions.

4. RESOLVE RESONANCE (Team Technique - UNIQUE & RARE)
What it is:

When two users with deeply compatible Convictions fight together
Their Resolve Energy synchronizes
Mutual power amplification
Extremely rare
Requirements (ALL must be met):

Both users must have compatible Convictions (not identical, but harmonious)
Genuine trust and emotional bond
Fighting side-by-side (physical proximity)
Willingness to open their Cores to each other (vulnerable)
Effects:

Both users feel each other's intent clearly
Power output increases (20-50% boost)
Can predict each other's movements instinctively
Shared pain tolerance (one takes a hit, both feel it less)
Combined techniques become possible
Visual:

Their auras visibly intertwine (colors merge/blend)
Synchronized breathing
Mirror-like movements
Almost telepathic coordination
Limitations:

Cannot be forced - either it happens naturally or not at all
If one user breaks trust, Resonance shatters permanently
Emotional conflict disrupts it
Only works between 2 people (no group Resonance)
Fractured users (like Tetsu) cannot Resonance while split
Why it's rare:

Requires perfect trust (rare among fighters)
Convictions must align philosophically (very rare)
Most fighters are too guarded to open their Cores
Naturals consider it shameful (sign of weakness)
Narrative Importance:

Tetsu and Aka achieving Resonance = major character milestone
Represents their true unification
Will be a pivotal story moment
Examples of compatible Convictions:

"I will protect everyone" + "I will never abandon my team" = Resonance possible
"I will become the strongest" + "I will prove I'm worthy" = Resonance impossible (competing egos)
