Jan 11
üî• SPEEDRUN MODE - SECTION 4: COMBAT RULES
A) POWER SCALING
How strength is measured:

GRADE SYSTEM (5 ‚Üí 0, lower = stronger)

GRADE 5: Weak Awakened, barely functional (most Lost)
GRADE 4: Average Awakened, basic control
GRADE 3: Competent fighters (most Division 7 members)
GRADE 2: Elite Awakened, refined techniques (Captain level)
GRADE 1: Top-tier, near-master level (rare)
GRADE 0: Absolute peak, world-class (Naturals, legends)
SPECIAL GRADE: Beyond measurement (Shin, possibly unified Tetsu)
Tetsu's progression:

Start: Grade 4 (struggling Fractured)
Mid-story: Grade 3 (competent)
Late-story: Grade 1 (elite)
Endgame: Special Grade (unified)
What determines grade:

Core stability
Conviction clarity
Technique mastery
Combat experience
Raw power output
B) RESOLVE DEPLETION
Energy levels:

100-70%: Full combat capability
70-40%: Noticeable fatigue, techniques weaken
40-20%: Heavy strain, abilities inconsistent
20-5%: Critical, survival mode only
5-0%: Collapse, defenseless
Warning signs:

Heavy breathing
Core area pain (chest tightness)
Aura flickering/dimming
Slower reactions
Technique failures
Consequences of hitting 0%:

Temporary unconsciousness
Vulnerable to Core attacks
Recovery takes hours/days
Repeated depletion damages Core permanently
C) CORE DAMAGE vs CORE DEATH
CORE DAMAGE (recoverable):

Cracks, fractures, partial breaks
Reduces maximum Resolve capacity
Causes chronic pain
Can heal with time/treatment (weeks to months)
Leaves permanent weaknesses
CORE DEATH (permanent):

Complete shattering
Becomes a "Hollow" - alive but empty
No willpower, no emotions, no drive
Essentially a walking vegetable
Fate worse than death
Cannot be reversed
How to cause Core Death:

Direct Core strike while target at 0% Resolve
Overwhelming sustained damage
Resolve Predation (stealing Core energy)
Certain forbidden techniques
D) RECOVERY METHODS
Natural recovery:

Rest + time
Moderate depletion: 6-12 hours
Severe depletion: 1-3 days
Core damage: weeks to months
Resolve Recovery Meditation:

Cuts recovery time in half
Requires safety and focus
Healing users (like Daichi):

Can speed physical recovery
Cannot restore Resolve Energy (only rest does that)
Can stabilize damaged Cores (prevent worsening)
Fractured users:

Recover 30% slower
More prone to Core damage
Harder to stabilize
E) COMBAT FLOW
Fight pacing:

Opening - Resolve Sense, Emission (feeling each other out)
Probing - Testing abilities, range, classification
Engagement - Full combat, technique exchanges
Climax - Finishing moves, desperation techniques
Resolution - Victory/defeat/retreat
Win conditions:

Knockout (unconscious)
Depletion (0% Resolve)
Surrender
Core damage (too injured to continue)
Death
Strategic elements:

Managing Resolve economy (don't waste energy)
Protecting your Core
Reading opponent's classification
Exploiting classification advantages
Timing power spikes
‚úÖ SECTION 4 COMPLETE
Power Scaling: Grade 5‚Üí0 system Depletion: 100%‚Üí0% with consequences Core Damage: Recoverable vs permanent death Recovery: Time + meditation + healing support Combat Flow: 5-phase structure

üéØ SECTION 5: UNIQUE PHENOMENA (FINAL RESOLVE SECTION)
Quick-fire definitions:

RESOLVE RESONANCE
Already defined in Universal Techniques ‚úì

RESOLVE CLASH
When two powerful attacks collide directly
Creates shockwave, reality distortion
Stronger Conviction wins
Can damage both fighters
Area devastation
RESOLVE PREDATION
Forbidden technique: stealing another's Resolve/Core
Extremely difficult, requires killing or complete domination
Predator absorbs victim's power
Highly unstable, often backfires
Used by main antagonists
RESOLVE BURN
Staking EVERYTHING on one attack
Channel 100% of remaining Resolve into single moment
If you succeed: devastating power
If you fail: Core shatters permanently
"All or nothing" move
THE LOST PHENOMENON
Chaotic Resolve without Conviction
Powers manifest randomly, violently
No control, no consciousness
Emit painful, corrupted Resolve signatures
Must be contained or killed
