What this accomplishes: ‚úÖ Sets tone and atmosphere ‚úÖ Reader understands stakes ‚úÖ Grounded, realistic feel ‚úÖ Strong sense of place

Risks: ‚ùå Slowest hook ‚ùå Can feel exposition-heavy ‚ùå Reader might skim

Best for: Readers who love world immersion, literary style

OPTION 5: DIALOGUE COLD OPEN (Voice-First)
Structure:

Open: Aka and Tetsu arguing
‚Üì
No context, just their dynamic
‚Üì
Reveals where they are through argument
‚Üì
Action interrupts conversation
Example Opening Line: "Let me kill it." "No." "You're going to die." "I said no."

What this accomplishes: ‚úÖ Personality first ‚úÖ Unique, punchy ‚úÖ Relationship established instantly ‚úÖ Voice-driven

Risks: ‚ùå Can feel disorienting ‚ùå Requires strong dialogue ‚ùå Context-light

Best for: Character chemistry focus, snappy tone

