üëÅÔ∏è HOW TO SPOT THE LOST (VISUAL/SENSORY CUES)
Since they look normal, we need subtle tells:

OPTION A: THE EYES
Eyes are "wrong" - too focused, too empty, or flickering
Color shifted (grayed out, or opposite: too vibrant)
Don't blink naturally
Stare too long
Pro: Classic, simple, works in any medium Con: Somewhat generic

OPTION B: RESOLVE SIGNATURE (Sense-based)
Resolve users can SENSE them
Their Resolve feels "corrupted" - like nails on chalkboard
Painful, discordant, wrong
Makes your Core ache to be near them
Pro: Fits your power system perfectly Con: Only works for Resolve users (civilians can't tell)

OPTION C: SHADOW BEHAVIOR
Their shadows move wrong
Slightly delayed, or too sharp
Darkness seems attracted to them
Lights flicker around them
Pro: Eerie, visual, symbolic Con: Might feel supernatural (breaks grounded tone?)

OPTION D: TEMPERATURE DROP
Area around them is subtly colder
Breath visible even in warm weather
Plants wilt near them
"Cold spot" phenomenon
Pro: Atmospheric, creepy Con: Could be hard to convey in all scenes

OPTION E: SPEECH PATTERN GLITCH
They speak normally but occasionally:
Repeat words unconsciously
Pause too long mid-sentence
Voice distorts for a syllable
Echo slightly
Pro: Subtle, unsettling, works in any medium Con: Needs careful writing to not feel gimmicky

OPTION F: PHYSICAL "TELL" (My Recommendation)
Combination approach:

Primary tell: BREATH VISIBLE (even in warm weather)

Their Core is "cold" - failed awakening froze something inside
You see their breath like it's winter
The closer you are, the colder it gets
Secondary tell: RESOLVE SENSE (for trained users)

Feels corrupted, painful to sense
Makes your own Core uncomfortable
Tertiary tell: EYES (on close inspection)

Pupils slightly dilated, or contracted
Don't react to light properly
"Dead" quality despite being alive
This gives you:

Visual cue anyone can spot (breath)
Sensory cue for Resolve users (sense)
Close-up detail for dramatic moments (eyes)
üéØ BETTER IDEA FOR THE CORE OF THE LOST?
