The Lost REJECTED what they saw
"I refuse this. I refuse to change. I refuse to accept this."
Their Anima awakened but their Conviction inverted
Result:

Conscious
Powered
But their Core is "negative" - built on rejection, not affirmation
They hate what they could have been
They hate everyone who accepted and moved forward
This explains:

Why they're hostile (they chose bitterness)
Why they can't be saved (they rejected salvation already)
Why they vary (Twisted, Philosophical, Broken - different rejections)
Why they're tragic (they made a choice, but during trauma)
Philosophically:

"You are what you refused to become"
Mirror to Tetsu (he could have been Lost if he rejected Aka)
Makes them sympathetic AND dangerous
