‚úÖ LOCKED - THE LOST (FINAL)
üé≠ THE LOST - TWO TYPES
TYPE 1: THE TWISTED (Common - 85%)
Nature:

Conscious, articulate, hateful
Despise society, humanity, normalcy
"The world failed me, so I'll burn it"
Pure malice and destructive nihilism
Dialogue:

Vitriolic, mocking, cruel
Blame everyone else
Enjoy causing pain
How to spot them:

Corrupted Resolve Sense (painful, discordant to sense)
Eyes (close inspection - pupils wrong, dead quality)
No temperature drop (normal body temp)
Morally: Irredeemable by choice, must be stopped

TYPE 2: THE PHILOSOPHICAL (Rare - 15%)
Nature:

Conscious, intelligent, ideological
See themselves as enlightened
Reject society's values/structure
"I awakened to the truth you're blind to"
Dialogue:

Calm, unsettling, questioning
Challenge morality and assumptions
Make you doubt yourself
Actually articulate arguments
How to spot them:

Temperature drop (area around them noticeably colder)
Visible breath (even in warm weather)
Corrupted Resolve Sense (but more controlled/focused)
Eyes (intensely aware, too focused)
Morally: Gray area, tragic villains, force deep questions

‚öñÔ∏è THE CORE PHILOSOPHY (WHAT HAUNTS RESOLVERS)
The Universal Truth:

"No matter how well-formed your Anima is, your Conviction is what runs along or against it‚Äîcreating a spectrum of good, bad, and gray."

What this means:

ANIMA = Your soul's raw energy (neutral)
Everyone has it
Can be pure, strong, refined
Not inherently good or evil
CONVICTION = Your certainty/will (directional)
What you believe absolutely
What drives you
This determines alignment
THE SPECTRUM:
GOOD (Conviction aligns with Anima positively):

"I will protect people"
"I will heal the wounded"
"I will stop evil"
Anima flows naturally, strengthens with use
GRAY (Conviction conflicts with Anima):

"I will survive no matter what"
"I will find the truth, regardless of cost"
"I will become strong, even if it hurts others"
Anima stutters, creates internal friction
This is where most people live
BAD (Conviction runs against Anima's nature):

"I will destroy everything"
"I will make them all suffer"
"I reject this world entirely"
Anima corrupts, becomes painful to use
This is The Lost
üî• THE HAUNTING IMPLICATION
Everyone asks themselves:

"Is my Conviction good? Or am I lying to myself?"

Because:

You can have pure Anima (strong soul)
But terrible Conviction (destructive will)
Result: Powerful monster
OR:

You can have weak Anima (fragile soul)
But noble Conviction (selfless will)
Result: Limited but heroic
The Lost are proof:

They had Anima (potential)
Their Conviction rejected everything (choice)
Now they're powerful AND destructive
The fear:

"What if MY Conviction is corrupted?"
"What if I'm becoming like them?"
"How do I know I'm on the right path?"
üé≠ HOW THIS AFFECTS CHARACTERS
TETSU:

Good Anima (dual cores, strong potential)
Conflicted Conviction ("I want to matter" - but WHY? For ego? For others?)
Gray spectrum - constantly questioning if he's good
AKA:

Shares Tetsu's Anima
Conviction: "Survive, dominate, don't be weak"
Gray leaning dark - but protective instincts contradict this
Not evil, but could be if pushed
THE TWISTED LOST:

Varying Anima quality
Conviction: "Burn it all"
Fully bad - chose destruction
THE PHILOSOPHICAL LOST:

Often STRONG Anima
Conviction: "Society is the disease, I am the cure"
Gray to bad - genuine belief they're right
Most dangerous because they're not mindless
PURE LINEAGES:

Refined Anima (generations of training)
Varying Convictions (some noble, some tyrannical)
Full spectrum - proves power ‚â† morality
üíÄ THE PHILOSOPHICAL LOST - DEEP THREAT
Why they're terrifying:

They can DEBATE you:

Lost: "You kill us to 'save' people. But who decided 
      their lives matter more than our freedom?"

Tetsu: "You're murdering innocents‚Äî"

