‚úÖ CHAPTER 1 STRUCTURE - FOR APPROVAL
üìñ CHAPTER 1: "TWO CORES"
Tone: Dark, visceral, character-driven with action POV: Third-person limited (Tetsu's perspective, but we hear Aka) Length: ~2,500-3,000 words Purpose: Introduce Tetsu, Aka, their dynamic, the world, R7, and The Lost

üé¨ STRUCTURE BREAKDOWN
OPENING (100-150 words)
Micro mundane moment ‚Üí immediate interruption

Tetsu tying his boots in R7 barracks
Aka's voice: comment about dying today
Tetsu's tired response (establishes their banter)
ALARM SCREAMS - mission call
Immediate transition to field deployment
Purpose:

10 seconds of character voice
Show dual personality instantly
Then IMMEDIATE action hook
SCENE 1: DEPLOYMENT (300-400 words)
R7 en route to incident

Setting:

Transport vehicle heading to abandoned district
2 months post-Epidemic Tokyo (show world state through description)
Present:

Tetsu
Kaito (friendly, worried about Tetsu)
Sara (sharp, observant, notices Tetsu's fatigue)
Daichi (quiet, preparing healing setup)
Captain Kurosawa (giving brief)
Captain's briefing:

"Lost spotted in industrial zone"
"Civilian evacuation complete"
"Contain or eliminate"
"Mikage, you're point. Prove you can handle this."
Tetsu's internal state:

Exhausted (didn't sleep)
Aka mocking him internally
Pressure to prove himself
Flashback snippet: why he joined R7 (wanted to matter, wanted family)
World-building through dialogue/description:

R7 patches on uniforms
Resolve Energy detectors mentioned
Public fear of "ability users"
Pure Lineages mentioned vaguely (context later)
End on: Vehicle stops. "We're here."

SCENE 2: THE HUNT (400-500 words)
Searching the abandoned district

Atmosphere:

Empty streets, quarantine zone aesthetic
Signs of Epidemic aftermath (abandoned belongings, graffiti, emptiness)
Eerie quiet
Squad spreads out:

Standard search pattern
Tetsu alone on east sector
Aka commenting on surroundings
Resolve Sense activates:

Tetsu feels something
Discordant, painful signature
"Found it."
Calls it in
The Lost appears:

Normal-looking person (30s, male, worn clothing)
No visible breath (Twisted type, not Philosophical)
Eyes have that "wrong" quality up close
Standing still, staring at Tetsu
Dialogue exchange:

Lost: "Another one of them."

Tetsu: "I don't want to fight you. Come quietly‚Äî"

Lost: [laughs bitterly] "Quietly? You people are hilarious."

Tetsu: "You're a Lost. You attacked civilians. I'm bringing you in."

Lost: "Lost? I'm awake. You're all still dreaming their dream."

Tetsu tries de-escalation (character trait: wants to save people)

Lost: "You think you're a hero? You're their dog."

Aka (internal): "He's not going to surrender. Stop wasting time."

Tetsu: "Last chance."

Lost: "No. Yours is."

Lost attacks.

SCENE 3: THE FIGHT - TETSU'S STRUGGLE (600-700 words)
Tetsu fighting, losing

Combat flow:

Initial exchange:

Tetsu raises barrier (Negation - Foresight/Rejection)
Lost uses [specific Resolve ability - maybe Assertion-type physical strikes]
Tetsu deflects first few attacks
Holding his own initially
Tetsu's internal monologue:

Analyzing patterns (Foresight)
Trying to predict, counter, control
Exhaustion creeping in
Aka's commentary:

"Left side, he favors‚Äî"
"You're too slow."
"Let me handle this."
Tetsu: (internal) Not yet. I can do this.
The Lost is TALKING while fighting:

"You joined them willingly?"
"What did they promise you? Purpose? Family?"
"You're just another tool."
Getting in Tetsu's head
Tetsu's performance degrades:

Slower reactions (sleep deprivation)
Heavier breathing
Core compression pain starting
The Lost lands a hit:

Claws across shoulder (Resolve-enhanced strike)
Blood sprays
Pain explodes
Second hit:

Ribs (crack)
Tetsu staggers
Third hit incoming:

Aimed at Core (chest)
Tetsu tries to block
Too slow
Aka (urgent): "SWITCH. NOW."

Tetsu refuses (stubborn pride):

"I've got‚Äî"
Hit connects (not direct Core, but close)
Tetsu's vision whites out
He's done
Aka takes over forcibly.

SCENE 4: THE SWITCH - AKA'S TURN (500-600 words)
Perspective shift: Aka in control

The switch:

Tetsu falls backward in their shared consciousness
Aka surges forward
Physical sensation: posture changes, expression hardens
Immediate difference:

Pain acknowledged but ignored
Black-red Resolve flares (Assertion - Momentum)
Pressure alone makes the Lost hesitate
Aka's fighting style:

Brutal, efficient, no wasted movement
Momentum Surge (kinetic enhancement)
Overwhelming offense
The Lost tries to talk: Lost: "Oh, so there ARE two of you‚Äî"

Aka: "Shut up."

Combat:

Aka catches the Lost's next attack
Uses momentum redirection
Slams Lost into ground (crater forms)
Doesn't give time to recover
Relentless, merciless
The Lost, pinned: Lost: "You're... just like me... rejected society..."

Aka: "Wrong. I just hate idiots."

Finishing move:

Not immediately lethal
Incapacitates completely (broken limbs, shattered Resolve)
Aka stands over defeated Lost:

Breathing steady
Looks at the wreckage of their body (Tetsu's injuries)
"Tch. Idiot."
SCENE 5: AFTERMATH (400-500 words)
R7 arrives, consequences

Kaito, Sara, Daichi arrive:

Firefight over
See Aka standing over the Lost
Tetsu's blood everywhere
Sara immediately: "That's not Tetsu."

Aka's response:

Flat, cold acknowledgment
"He's fine. Mostly."
Daichi moves to heal:

Asks Aka to switch back
Aka: "Can't. He's out."
Captain Kurosawa arrives:

Surveys scene
"Report."
Aka gives facts: Lost contained, no civilian casualties, Mikage's injuries
Captain: "Bring the Lost in. Alive."

Aka: "He attacked‚Äî"

Captain: "Alive. That's an order."

Tension:

Aka doesn't take orders well
But Kurosawa's Resolve pressure (golden aura) weighs down
Standoff moment
Aka complies (barely):

Restrains the Lost (still alive, unconscious)
Daichi begins healing Tetsu's body while Aka controls it
Quiet moment:

Daichi: "How is he? Inside?"
Aka: "...Sleeping. Like I said."
Sara: "You protected him."
Aka: [no response, looks away]
Transport arrives:

Lost loaded for containment
Tetsu's body treated
R7 returns to base
Final beat:

Inside their shared consciousness
Camera pulls into Tetsu's perspective (unconscious, floating in dark)
Aka's voice, distant: "You're welcome, idiot."
CLOSING (100-150 words)
Set up next chapter hook

Tetsu waking up:

Medical bay
Body bandaged
Kaito sitting nearby (keeping watch)
Kaito: "Hey. You're back."

Tetsu: [groggy] "What... happened?"

Kaito: "Aka saved your ass. Again."

Tetsu tries to sit up, winces

Kaito: "Captain wants to see you. When you're ready."

Tetsu: "...The Lost?"

Kaito: "Contained. Alive. For now."

Tetsu: [internal] Aka?

Aka's voice: "I'm here. And you're still an idiot."

Final line:

Tetsu closes his eyes
Knows they need to talk
Knows Captain's going to chew him out
Knows he fucked up
End Chapter 1.

