Normal
Then the voice: "My turn."

Tetsu's hand moves without his input. Waves mockingly.

Tetsu panics: "Stop‚Äî"

"Relax. I'm not taking over. Just... showing you how this works."

The hand returns to his control.

Tetsu: "How is this‚Äîwhat happened to me?"

"We awakened. Split Cores. Two Convictions, one body. Congratulations. We're a freak even among freaks."

Tetsu tries to process:

Turns on TV (still news coverage)
"Thousands affected by mysterious illness"
"Some showing unusual abilities"
"Government forming response teams"
"Please report to nearest medical facility"
The voice: "You're not going anywhere. They'll lock us up or worse."

Tetsu: "We need help‚Äî"

"We need to survive. That's it."

First test of abilities:

Tetsu feels something in his chest
Energy? Power?
Reaches for it instinctively
Pale blue light flickers around his hand
Resolve Energy
The voice: "Not bad. Now let me try."

Tetsu: "No‚Äî"

Too late.

The switch happens involuntarily:

Tetsu falls backward in consciousness
Suddenly standing in his apartment (mental construct forms)
Watching through distant eyes
The Other takes control:

Black-red energy replaces blue
Posture shifts
Tests the body, flexing, moving
"Hm. Weak. But workable."
30 seconds later, Tetsu snaps back to control.

Gasping, terrified.

The Other: "See? We share. Whether you like it or not."

SCENE 5: THE AGREEMENT (400-500 words)
Forming the fragile pact

The next few hours:

Tetsu tries to understand what happened
The Other explains (mockingly, but informative)
"The illness wasn't illness. It was awakening."
"Your soul cracked. Now there's two of us."
Tetsu: "Can we... separate?"

The Other: "No. We're stuck. Two Cores, one body. Deal with it."

Testing control:

They switch back and forth
Tetsu learns he can hold control as long as he stays focused
But exhaustion, pain, fear‚Äîany weakness‚Äîand The Other can take over
The Other: "You're the default. I'm the backup. But when you fail‚Äîand you will‚ÄîI step in."

Tetsu: "I didn't ask for this."

The Other: "Neither did I. But here we are."

The Pact (informal, first version):

Tetsu: "If we're stuck together... we need rules."

The Other: "Fine. You get the body most of the time. But when you're about to get us killed, I take over. Non-negotiable."

Tetsu: "And you give it back after?"

The Other: "...Eventually."

Not a promise. But close enough.

Final beat:

Tetsu looks at his reflection
Two people in one body
"What do I even call you?"
The Other: "Don't. I'm not a person. I'm just... the other one."

Tetsu: "The Other."

The Other: "Sure. Whatever."

Silence.

Then:

The Other: "You wanted to matter, right? To be seen? Well, congratulations. You got your wish."

Tetsu stares at his hands:

Pale blue flickers around his fingers
Power he doesn't understand
A voice he didn't choose
A future he can't predict
But alive.

And for the first time in years: Not alone.

CLOSING (150-200 words)
Bridge to present, one week later

Time skip: One week post-Epidemic

Tetsu has survived:

Figured out basics (Resolve Sense, control, switching)
Avoided government roundups (barely)
Living day-to-day
The Other: "We need a plan. Can't hide forever."

Tetsu: "I know."

Knock on door.

Both freeze.

Voice outside: "Tetsu Mikage? I'm Captain Kurosawa. Tokyo Resolvers. We know you're Awakened. We're here to help."

Tetsu and The Other (simultaneous thought): This is it.

Tetsu opens door.

Kurosawa stands there, golden aura subdued, R7 wristband visible.

Kurosawa: "You have two choices. Come with us and learn to control your abilities. Or run, and we find you anyway."

Tetsu: "...What if I come with you?"

Kurosawa: "Then you join R7. You protect people. You matter."

The Other: "He's offering exactly what you wanted."

Tetsu looks at Kurosawa.

"I'll come."

Kurosawa nods.

"Welcome to the Resolvers."

End Chapter 2.

