R7 wristband glowing steady pale blue
The Other's voice:

"About time. Captain's been waiting three hours."
Tetsu: "Let him wait."
"Brave words for someone who passed out like a baby."
Kaito enters:

"Oh good, you're up. Captain wants you. Now."
Hands Tetsu his casual clothes (washed, folded)
"Also, Ayaka says you fight like shit when you're tired. Her words."
Transition:

Tetsu dresses, heads to Captain's office
Building tension
SCENE 1: THE LORE BOMB (900-1000 words)
Captain Kurosawa's office

Setting:

Spartan office, no decorations
Just desk, chairs, filing cabinets
One photo frame (face-down‚ÄîKurosawa's private grief)
Kurosawa sitting, waiting:

"Sit."
Tetsu sits
Long silence
The conversation begins:

Kurosawa: "Do you know what you are, Mikage?"

Tetsu: "...Awakened. Fractured. Dual cores."

Kurosawa: "You're a problem."

Pause.

Kurosawa: "Not your fault. But a problem nonetheless."

He opens a file. Slides it across.

Inside: Photos of Pure Lineage clan crests.

Kurosawa: "You've heard of Pure Lineages?"

Tetsu: "Vaguely. Old families with Resolve before the Epidemic?"

Kurosawa: "Four major clans in Japan. Kurosawa. Sanada. Hayami. Yomotsu."

Points to each crest.

Kurosawa: "For centuries, we controlled Resolve. Kept it secret. Told the world only bloodlines could wield it."

Tetsu: "...You lied."

Kurosawa: "We maintained order. Resolve in untrained hands is catastrophic. You've seen The Lost."

The Other (internal): "So they're the reason we were invisible. Nice."

Kurosawa continues:

"The Epidemic broke our monopoly. Thousands of commoners awakened. You. Kaito. Ayaka. Daichi. All proof the myth was false."

"Some clans adapted. Mine cooperated with the government, formed R7."

"Others... didn't."

Leans forward.

Kurosawa: "Sanada wants you, Mikage."

Tetsu's stomach drops.

Tetsu: "Why?"

Kurosawa: "Dual cores. Unprecedented. If they can recruit you‚Äîbring you into their clan, offer you resources, training, status‚Äîthey gain a living symbol."**

"Proof that even 'mistakes' like you can be molded. Controlled."

The Other: "They want to OWN us."

Tetsu: "And if I refuse?"

Kurosawa: "They'll try harder. Sanada doesn't accept refusal well."**

Pause.

Tetsu: "What about R7? Who actually runs it?"**

Kurosawa: "Good question."**

THE REVEAL:

Kurosawa: "Officially? Government oversight, Pure Lineage consultation."**

"Reality? Tokyo R7 is privately funded."

Tetsu: "By who?"**

Kurosawa: "A disbanded clan member. Yomotsu lineage."**

The name hangs in the air.

Tetsu: "I thought Yomotsu was extinct."**

Kurosawa: "Officially, yes. Destroyed centuries ago. Erased from records."**

"But one survived. Went underground. Built R7 as... penance, perhaps. Or insurance."

Tetsu: "Do I get to meet them?"**

Kurosawa: "Eventually. When they decide you're ready."**

"For now, know this: R7 answers to no clan. Not Kurosawa. Not Sanada. We're neutral ground."

"That's why you're safe here. But only here."

END SCENE - LORE BOMB DROPPED

###SCENE 2: PROCESSING (300-400 words) Hallway, Tetsu walking back

Internal dialogue with The Other:

"So we're a political football."

Tetsu: (internal) Yeah.

"And Sanada wants to recruit us like we're some prize horse."

Tetsu: Pretty much.

"...I hate this already."

Tetsu: You and me both.

Ayaka appears, leaning against wall:

"Captain chew you out?"

Tetsu: "Something like that."

Ayaka: "You look like you just learned Santa isn't real."

Tetsu: "Worse. I learned we're all pawns in a centuries-old power game."

Ayaka: "Oh. Yeah. That."

She pushes off wall.

Ayaka: "Welcome to being Awakened. It sucks. But R7's still the best option."

Tetsu: "You knew? About the clans?"

Ayaka: "Some. Captain doesn't hide it from veterans. Figured you'd learn eventually."

She starts walking. Tetsu follows.

Ayaka: "Come on. Downtime. You've earned it."

SCENE 3: DOWNTIME - R7 APARTMENT (800-900 words)
Casual bonding, character development

Setting:

Shared apartment (Tetsu, Kaito, Ayaka all crash here)
Modest but lived-in
Kaito's mess everywhere, Ayaka's corner pristine
Kaito cooking (surprisingly well):

"You're back! Alive! Not retired!"
Making curry
Offers Tetsu a bowl
Sitting together:

Casual conversation
Kaito talks about his family (avoided them post-Epidemic)
Ayaka mentions her training (learned weapons young, private tutors‚Äîhints at wealth)
The Other's coin:

Kaito notices:

"Hey, you keep flipping that coin."
Tetsu looks confused: "What coin?"
Realizes his hand IS holding a coin
Doesn't remember taking it out
The Other: "It's mine."

Tetsu: (internal) Since when?

The Other: "Since the Epidemic. You never noticed."

Ayaka: "Let me see."

Tetsu hands it over.

It's bent. Worn. Both sides look identical (damaged during the split).

Ayaka: "Heads and tails are the same."

The Other: "Exactly."

Ayaka hands it back, suspicious but says nothing.

Quiet moment:

They eat together
First time Tetsu's felt... normal since awakening
Family feeling
Kaito: "So, dual cores. That mean you're twice as strong?"

Tetsu: "More like twice as complicated."

Ayaka: "You switching mid-fight was weird. But effective."

Kaito: "The Other seems... intense."

Tetsu: "That's one word for it."

SCENE 4: MENTAL SPACE - CHARACTER PEAK (600-700 words)
That night, Tetsu alone in his room

He lies down, closes eyes.

Enters the mental space (apartment construct).

The Other is there, sitting on the couch, flipping the coin.

First real conversation:

Tetsu: "We need to talk."

The Other: "About?"

Tetsu: "Everything. The Epidemic. The split. Why you remember things I don't."

The Other stops flipping the coin.

The Other: "You really want to know?"

Tetsu: "Yeah."

Pause.

The Other: "During the hallucinations... when the voice was breaking you down... I was forming. Watching. Learning."

*"I saw things. Felt things. Memories that aren't from this life."

Tetsu: "What do you mean, 'this life'?"

The Other looks at him. Expression unreadable.

The Other: "I don't know yet. Just... echoes. Faces I don't recognize. A name I can't remember."

*"And a feeling like I've done this before."

Tetsu's skin prickles.

Tetsu: "Done what?"

The Other: "Died. And come back."

Silence.

Tetsu: "You think we've... lived before?"

The Other: "I think YOU have. And I'm the part that remembers."

He stands, pockets the coin.

The Other: "But I'm not ready to talk about it yet. Neither are you."

Tetsu: "When will we be?"

The Other: "When it matters."

He walks toward the door (mental construct boundary).

The Other: "Get some sleep. Tomorrow's going to be worse."

Tetsu: "How do you know?"

The Other turns back, smirking slightly.

The Other: "Because it always is."

He fades. Tetsu alone in the space.

CHARACTER PEAK MOMENT: Tetsu whispers:

"Do you want a name? A real one?"

The Other's voice, distant:

"...Maybe. But not yet. 'The Other' works for now."

"It reminds us both: we're stuck. Two sides, same coin."

Tetsu looks at his hands. Feels the weight of everything.

SCENE 5: THE WATCHER (400-500 words)
Late night, Tetsu can't sleep

Goes to apartment balcony.

City lights below. Tokyo recovering, slowly.

He activates Resolve Sense idly. Just feeling the area.

Normal signatures. R7 members nearby. Civilians sleeping.

Then‚Äî

Something else.

Distant. Faint. But WRONG.

Not corrupted like The Lost.

Just... old. Heavy. Ancient.

Tetsu's Core aches just sensing it.

He focuses. Tries to pinpoint‚Äî

Gone.

Like it was never there.

The Other: "You felt that?"

Tetsu: "Yeah. What was it?"

The Other: "...I don't know. But I've felt it before."

Tetsu: "When?"

The Other: "In the memories I don't understand."

Tetsu scans again. Nothing.

But the feeling lingers.

Someone was watching.

END CHAPTER 3 - OMINOUS HOOK

‚úÖ CHAPTER 3 SUMMARY
What it accomplishes:

‚úì LORE BOMB - Pure Lineages revealed, R7's true nature exposed, Yomotsu backer introduced
‚úì Character Peak - First deep Tetsu/Other conversation, past life hints, coin symbolism deepened
‚úì Downtime - R7 family bonding, normalcy contrast, humor beats
‚úì Threat Setup - Mystery watcher (Shin's first presence, or Sanada spy)
‚úì Escalation - Every element raises stakes or deepens mystery

Pacing:

Opens tense (Captain's office)
Peaks with lore (worldbuilding expansion)
Softens (downtime, bonding)
Emotional (mental space conversation)
Ends ominous (watcher hook)
Cliffhanger: Someone ancient is watching Tetsu. Who? Why?

